MaritalStatus <- as.character(SalesData$marriage)

#N <- MaritalStatus[nchar(MaritalStatus)==0]
#sub(s,'N',MaritalStatus)
#sub('NoneMarried','Married',MaritalStatus)
k <- 1
k1<-1
for (s in MaritalStatus) {
    if (s==''){
      #print(s)
      MaritalStatus[k1]='Divorced/None'
      k=k+1
    }
    k1=k1+1
}
cat ('k ',k)
## k  14028
Sales_MaritalStatus <-ggplot(SalesData,aes(x=MaritalStatus)) + 
  geom_bar(aes(fill=SalesData$online),position = "fill")+
  theme_classic()+
  labs(title="Marital Status VS Purchased on social networking",
       x="Marital Status",y="Rate")

AgeStatus <- as.character(SalesData$age) #1_Unk
k <- 1
k1<-1
for (s in AgeStatus) {
  if (s=='1_Unk'){
    #print(s)
    AgeStatus[k1]='4_<=45'
    k=k+1
  }
  k1=k1+1
}

Sales_Age <-ggplot(SalesData,aes(x=AgeStatus)) + 
  geom_density(aes(fill=SalesData$online),alpha=0.7)+

social_Ads <- read.csv('Ads.csv')
Purchased.code <- as.character(social_Ads$Purchased)
Purchased.code[Purchased.code=="1"]="No"
Purchased.code[Purchased.code=="0"]="Yes"
social_Ads <- data.frame(social_Ads,Purchased.code)
attach(social_Ads)
